The paper deals with the construction of binary self-dual codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of group rings and block matrices suggests a connection to algebraic coding theory (cs.CC) and combinatorial designs (cs.DM). The paper also employs a generalised neighbour method, which is a technique used in cryptography (cs.CR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
